\section{Drawing helpers}

%ul = upper left
%lr = lower right
%claude:
[<pl_relief()>] draws a 3D {relief} border around a rectangle
using two colors: [[ul]] (upper-left edges) and [[lr]] (lower-right
edges).
When [[ul]] is light and [[lr]] is dark, the widget appears raised;
swapping them makes it appear sunken.
The nested loop fills the diagonal corner pixels where the
horizontal and vertical edges meet.

%TODO: FIGURE: screenshot

<<function [[pl_relief]]>>=
void pl_relief(Image *b, Image *ul, Image *lr, Rectangle r, int wid){
    int x, y;

    draw(b, Rect(r.min.x, r.max.y-wid, r.max.x, r.max.y), lr, 0, ZP);/* bottom*/
    draw(b, Rect(r.max.x-wid, r.min.y, r.max.x, r.max.y), lr, 0, ZP);/* right */
    draw(b, Rect(r.min.x, r.min.y, r.min.x+wid, r.max.y), ul, 0, ZP);/* left */
    draw(b, Rect(r.min.x, r.min.y, r.max.x, r.min.y+wid), ul, 0, ZP);/* top */

    for(x=0;x!=wid;x++) 
      for(y=wid-1-x;y!=wid;y++){
        draw(b, rectaddpt(Rect(0,0,1,1), Pt(x+r.max.x-wid, y+r.min.y)), lr, 0, ZP);
        draw(b, rectaddpt(Rect(0,0,1,1), Pt(x+r.min.x, y+r.max.y-wid)), lr, 0, ZP);
    }
}
@
%SCREENSHOT where see relief effect thanks to just 2 colors.
% often white is ul and black is lr (for shadow effect)

%claude:
The four [[draw()]] calls paint the four edges of the border:
\begin{verbatim}
  r.min.x          r.max.x
  r.min.y +--ul--ul--ul--+
          |ul            |lr
          |ul            |lr
          |ul            |lr
  r.max.y +--lr--lr--lr--+
          |<--- wid --->|

          ul = upper-left color (top + left edges)
          lr = lower-right color (bottom + right edges)
\end{verbatim}
The nested loop fills the two diagonal corners (top-right and
bottom-left) where the [[ul]] and [[lr]] edges meet, painting
them with [[lr]] to create a clean mitered join.

